#. <section class="sutta" id="sn17.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 10. Sagāthakasutta → sagāthasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn17.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Sagāthakasutta"
msgstr "10. With Verses"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.10:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.2"
msgid "“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya."
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …"

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi sakkārena abhibhūtaṃ "
"pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapannaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Take a case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome and "
"overwhelmed by honor. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi asakkārena abhibhūtaṃ "
"pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapannaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Take another case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome and "
"overwhelmed by lack of honor. When their body breaks up, after death, they’"
"re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ passāmi sakkārena ca asakkārena ca "
"tadubhayena abhibhūtaṃ pariyādiṇṇacittaṃ, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ "
"duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And take another case where I see a certain person whose mind is overcome "
"and overwhelmed by both honor and lack of honor. When their body breaks up, "
"after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, "
"hell."

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …"
msgstr ""
"That’s how brutal, bitter, and harsh are possessions, honor, and popularity. "
"…”"

msgctxt "sn17.10:1.7"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.10:2.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn17.10:2.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.10:3.1"
msgid "“Yassa sakkariyamānassa,"
msgstr "“Whether they’re honored"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:3.2"
msgid "asakkārena cūbhayaṃ;"
msgstr "or not honored, or both,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:3.3"
msgid "Samādhi na vikampati,"
msgstr "their immersion doesn’t waver"

# I feel appamada is a better fit here.
#. <br>
#. VAR: appamāṇavihārino → appamādaviharino (pts1-2) | appamādavihārino (mr)
msgctxt "sn17.10:3.4"
msgid "appamāṇavihārino."
msgstr "as they live diligently."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ jhāyinaṃ sātatikaṃ,"
msgstr "They regularly practice absorption"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.2"
msgid "sukhumaṃ diṭṭhivipassakaṃ;"
msgstr "with subtle view and discernment."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.3"
msgid "Upādānakkhayārāmaṃ,"
msgstr "Rejoicing in the end of grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.4"
msgid "āhu sappuriso itī”ti."
msgstr "they’re said to be a good person.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.10:4.6"
msgid "Paṭhamo vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.10:5.1"
msgid "Dāruṇo baḷisaṃ kummaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:5.2"
msgid "dīghalomi ca mīḷhakaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:5.3"
msgid "Asani diddhaṃ siṅgālaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn17.10:5.4"
msgid "verambhena sagāthakanti."
msgstr ""
